reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I've never been this excited about a fan extension cable!
reviews.reviewText: I don't leave many product reviews, especially for inexpensive items. However, I am really impressed with these fan extension cables. The black nylon braided exterior has a premium quality look and feel, and the connector ends are tightly rapped in rubber. I have previously paid about the same price for a single fan extension cable so the 5-pack makes this an extremely outstanding value. I highly recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's a fan extender
reviews.reviewText: Decent quality, actual 4 pin connectors which is nice. Sometimes the cheap ones are only 2 or 3 actual wires in the connector.I ended up needing to modify a couple of them & do some soldering to make a Y connector, project changed a little along the way. But! Worked great, can recommend 👍🏼

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: I bought these for a new computer build. Some of the fans came with very short cords, barely long enough to reach the connectors on the motherboard, and not long enough for the way I wished to route the cords. First, when I received these cords, I noted how good of a quality they were. Second, they allowed me to route the fan power cables the way I wanted to so that my computer had a much cleaner look. Made it possible to ensure I can add and remove components without the cords getting in the way. Very pleased!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great extension cable
reviews.reviewText: Got these extension cables to reach a front fan from the last remaining port at the other far end of the case near the I/O shield of the motherboard. Worked great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars nice extensions, heat shrink is cheap
reviews.reviewText: These do exactly what I needed them to do.One downfall is the heat-shrink tubing does not adhere to the sleeving well, and if you bend the cable end to a 90 degree in order to fit into a snug space, the sleeving will come out of the heat shrink. BUT, I have also used more expensive brands and occasionally they do it as well. So, for the money, it's to be expected.Good value with the amount/length of extensions in the kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality and worked as expected
reviews.reviewText: I was hesitant to purchase these extension cables, but it worked like a charm. My Asus motherboard did not have any trouble detecting the fan and I really glad it works as expected.
